  m_Name: Atlas of Forgotten Realms
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  bookTitle: Atlas of Forgotten Realms
  coverImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 8d4f251c256a6b94083b207624b6b4b7, type: 3}
  worldIcon: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 8d4f251c256a6b94083b207624b6b4b7, type: 3}
  pageContent: '"...East of the Misty Mountains lie the ruins of Eldria. Once its
    spires touched the clouds and the streets were paved with silver. Now there is
    only the whisper of the wind in empty halls. They say that if you light a blue
    fire in the center of the main square, you can see shadows of the past. But be
    careful: those who look at ghostly Eldria for too long forget the way home and
    remain there as eternal guests..."'
